<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-04-07T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-04-07T15:00:00-05:00" n="585" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d585">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00/2814: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Commissioner in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Welles</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-04-07T15:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">April 7,
                                        1924—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>13. Your 23, March 25, 9 a.m. Department informed by Secretary of the
                            Navy that he has decided to keep General Lee in his office as Military
                            Governor until after July 1, and has therefore directed that the order
                            for his relief in April be revoked.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>